    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 256,
    "last_activity_date" : 1524607214,
    "last_edit_date" : 1524607214,
    "creation_date" : 1287240948,
    "answer_id" : 3949379,
    "question_id" : 3949260,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><code>clazz.isAssignableFrom(Foo.class)</code> will be true whenever the class represented by the <code>clazz</code> object is a superclass or superinterface of <code>Foo</code>.</p>\n\n<p><code>clazz.isInstance(obj)</code> will be true whenever the object <code>obj</code> is an instance of the class <code>clazz</code>.</p>\n\n<p>That is: </p>\n\n<pre><code>clazz.isAssignableFrom(obj.getClass()) == clazz.isInstance(obj)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>is always true so long as <code>clazz</code> and <code>obj</code> are nonnull.</p>\n"
  }, {
